text: Hey everyone. I'm a full-time freelance writer, mostly focusing on blogs and occasional whitepaper. Right now, my clients are mostly in finance and insurance (especially B2B insurance like workers' comp), though I have written for some SaaS tools in these fields and dabbled a bit in real estate, both residential and more recently commercial. I'm here because I want to improve my writing and also look at some ways to level up into defined opportunities for content strategy, audits, and the like. I know this is the place to really get into learning more about that so I'm looking forward to it. I also want to get more defined in a niche and sort of overall focused. 2020 has been my best year ever income-wise and this feels like a good opportunity to make some tweaks.
